  "caveats": [
    "The fresh Windows reruns record git_dirty true because the new direct CLI helper and its test registration were already present. The replay, Monte Carlo, reporting and dashboard runtime code paths still matched HEAD b3f9534a815993867160f7ba247ff5957fb032f4.",
    "The monitored runtime suite includes process-tree sampling and records one warm measured run per cell, so short-case throughput claims should be cross-checked against the direct CLI reruns in the same review root.",
    "The WSL deployment-shape reruns came from a synced Linux-filesystem checkout whose Git metadata still reported eafb1e48828118334fbda391f4fec33099c39b42 and git_dirty true, so they are deployment-shape evidence rather than clean-commit Git proof.",
    "WSL tree RSS is still a summed RSS measure. Fork-shared pages can inflate pack-level totals, so use the targeted Monte Carlo cells and the 5 ms frontier probes for the cleanest cross-environment memory reading.",
    "A fresh same-machine Chris Roberts rerun was not possible in this session because the exact local repo path from the earlier audited run was no longer present. The preserved audited report remains the best local external reference evidence, but it is historical rather than fresh-current.",
    "The shared-memory result is a transport microbenchmark only, not end-to-end Monte Carlo proof."
